<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - FRONT BEARING COVER AND INPUT SHAFT
        NUT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>FRONT BEARING COVER AND INPUT SHAFT NUT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts, drive gear bearing cover and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018c2">Figure 122</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018c2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018c2" filename="../figg13/G13018c2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 122. Remove Bolts, Drive Gear Bearing Cover, and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the oil seal from the cover of models so equipped (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018c3">Figure 123</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018c3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018c3" filename="../figg13/G13018c3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 123. Remove Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage the two mainshaft sliding clutches into gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018c4">Figure 124</hotlnk>); this prevents the transmission from rotating. Remove nut
                (left hand thread) with the drive gear nut removing tool.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018c4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018c4" filename="../figg13/G13018c4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 124. Engage Mainshaft Sliding Clutches into Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
